JOHANNESBURG - South Africa’s Kevin Anderson maintained his career-high ranking of eighth in the ATP singles rankings on Monday. The 31-year-old first reached No 8 in the world on February 26. READ: Kevin Anderson holds nerve to win New York Open The South African started 2017 at No 80 in the ATP Rankings after an injury-ravaged 2016. It was his lowest mark since August 2010. Anderson reached a then career-high ranking of 10th in October 2015 soon after beating Britain’s Andy Murray to reach the US Open quarterfinals. Next best among the men is Lloyd Harris, who is ranked 246th. Other SA rankings: 355: Nik Scholtz 648: Ruan Roelofse 1,193: Siphos Montsi 1,412: Tucker Vorster 1,588: Joshua Howard-Tripp 1,588: Kholo Montsi 1,680: Lleyton Cronje African News Agency